<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-561] NullPointerException in Invodker.toTypeString if arg is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-561</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Invoker.toTypeString method blows up with a NullPointerException if one of the arguments is null.   The NullPointerException occurs on Invoker.java, line 439:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    argBuf.append(arguments&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.getClass().getName());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An argument might be null for example if a builder is invoked with a class parameter that either does not exist or has not been imported.  For example, a PicoContainerBuidler:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    builder.container() &lt;/p&gt;
{
      component(class : WhoopsIMadeATypo)
    }

&lt;p&gt;The &apos;WhoopsIMadeATypo&apos; arg shows up as null in the arguments array passed to Invoker.toString.  So we get a NullPointerException Invoker.toString, which makes it really hard to figure out the real cause.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple null-check guard would fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
